   - Market analysis and key trends affecting the strategy
   - Competitive landscape review
   - Internal capabilities and gap assessment

3. STRATEGIC GOALS
   ${goalsList}

4. RESOURCE ALLOCATION
   ${resourcesList}

5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP
   - Phase 1 (0-3 months): Quick wins and foundational setup
   - Phase 2 (3-6 months): Core initiative execution
   - Phase 3 (6-12 months): Scale, optimize, and expand

6. KPIs AND METRICS
   - Define 2-3 success metrics per strategic goal
   - Set quarterly review cadence and reporting structure
   - Identify leading and lagging indicators

Constraints:
- Each strategic goal must have at least one measurable KPI
- The timeline must be realistic given available resources
- Include risk factors and mitigation strategies for each phase
- Consider dependencies between phases and goals
- Tone: Strategic, confident, and action-oriented. Use business planning language.`;
            break;
          }
          case 'research-paper': {
            if (!v.topic) break;
            output = `You are an academic research advisor. Draft a research paper on ${v.topic}.

Context: The paper's thesis is: ${v.thesis || 'To be developed through the research process'}. The methodology will be ${v.methodology || 'defined based on the research questions'}.${v.sources ? ' Key sources include:\n' + v.sources : ''}

Paper Structure:

1. TITLE
   - Working title that reflects the core contribution

2. ABSTRACT
   - Brief summary of research question, methods, key findings, and conclusions (150-250 words)

3. INTRODUCTION
   - Background and context for ${v.topic} — why this research matters
   - Research problem and its significance
   - Specific research questions or hypotheses
   - Thesis statement: ${v.thesis || 'State your thesis'}
   - Paper structure overview for reader orientation

4. LITERATURE REVIEW
   - Key theories and frameworks relevant to ${v.topic}
   - Current state of research — what is known and what gaps remain
   - How this paper addresses identified gaps
   - Critical evaluation of prior work

5. METHODOLOGY
   - Research approach: ${v.methodology || 'Qualitative, quantitative, or mixed methods'}
   - Data collection and sampling methods
   - Analysis techniques and validation approach
   - Limitations and delimitations

6. FINDINGS/ANALYSIS
   - Presentation of results with appropriate visualizations
   - Statistical or thematic analysis

7. DISCUSSION
   - Interpretation of findings in context of existing literature
   - Implications for theory, practice, or policy

8. CONCLUSION
   - Summary of key findings and contributions
   - Limitations of the study
   - Future research directions
   - Practical or theoretical implications

Constraints:
- Each section must have a clear purpose and connection to the thesis
- Use formal academic language throughout — do not use contractions or colloquialisms
- Include citations in appropriate academic format (APA, MLA, Chicago)
- Ensure logical flow between sections with clear transitions
- Tone: Academic, objective, and authoritative. Maintain third-person perspective.`;
            break;
          }
          case 'data-analysis': {
            if (!v.dataset) break;
            output = `You are a senior data analyst. Analyze the following dataset:
${v.dataset}

Context: The analysis aims to answer: ${v.questions || 'key questions about the data'}. The techniques to apply include: ${v.techniques || 'appropriate statistical and analytical methods'}. The desired output is ${v.output || 'a comprehensive analysis report'}.

Analysis Plan:

1. DATA UNDERSTANDING
   - Assess dataset size, structure, and quality
   - Identify variable types and distributions
   - Evaluate missing data, outliers, and data quality issues

2. EXPLORATORY ANALYSIS
   - Compute descriptive statistics for all key variables
   - Create visualizations: distributions, correlations, trends over time
   - Generate initial hypotheses based on patterns observed

3. ANALYSIS APPROACH
   - Apply techniques: ${v.techniques || 'select appropriate statistical tests or ML models'}
   - Define validation strategy (train/test split, cross-validation)
   - Specify success criteria and significance thresholds

4. KEY QUESTIONS TO ANSWER
${v.questions ? v.questions.split('\n').filter(Boolean).map(q => `   - ${q}`).join('\n') : '   - Define primary and secondary research questions'}

5. DELIVERABLES
   - ${v.output || 'Analysis report with visualizations, key insights, and actionable recommendations'}
   - Document code, methodology, and assumptions
   - Include limitations and caveats

Constraints:
- Begin with data quality assessment before any analysis
- Use appropriate statistical significance levels (p < 0.05)
- Do not overstate conclusions — clearly separate findings from interpretations
- Include visualization recommendations for each key finding
- Document all assumptions and methodological choices
- Tone: Analytical, precise, and data-driven. Use statistical terminology correctly.`;
            break;
          }
          case 'lesson-plan': {
            if (!v.topic) break;
            output = `You are an experienced educator and curriculum designer. Create a lesson plan on ${v.topic}.

Context: The lesson is designed for ${v.level || 'beginner'} level students and will run for ${v.duration || 'approximately 60 minutes'}. The learning objectives guide all instructional activities.

Learning Objectives:
${v.objectives || '- Define and explain key concepts related to ' + v.topic + '\n- Apply knowledge through practical exercises\n- Demonstrate understanding through assessment activities'}

Lesson Structure:

1. OPENING (5-10 minutes)
   - Hook or attention-getter related to ${v.topic}
   - Connect to prior knowledge and real-world relevance
   - State learning objectives clearly

2. DIRECT INSTRUCTION (15-20 minutes)
   - Present core content with clear explanations and examples
   - Use demonstrations, visuals, or multimedia to support learning
   - Check for understanding every 5 minutes with quick questions

3. GUIDED PRACTICE (15-20 minutes)
   - Hands-on activity or exercise applying the concepts
   - Work through examples together with scaffolded support
   - Provide immediate feedback and correction

4. INDEPENDENT PRACTICE (10-15 minutes)
   - Student-led application without direct guidance
   - Formative assessment to gauge individual understanding
   - Differentiate tasks for varying ability levels

5. CLOSING (5-10 minutes)
   - Review and summarize key takeaways
   - Exit ticket or quick assessment of learning objectives
   - Preview next lesson and assign relevant practice

Materials Needed:
- [List all required materials, handouts, technology, and preparation]

Assessment:
- Formative: Observations, questioning, exit ticket
- Summative: [Project, quiz, or performance task measuring stated objectives]

Constraints:
- Each learning objective must be addressed by at least one activity
- Include differentiation strategies for at least two ability levels
- Allocate time realistically — account for transitions between activities
- Use active learning techniques — minimize lecture time
- Tone: Instructional, clear, and engaging. Write for the educator delivering the lesson.`;
            break;
          }
          case 'study-guide': {
            if (!v.subject) break;
            output = `You are an expert tutor and study guide creator. Create a comprehensive study guide for ${v.subject}.

Context: This study guide covers ${v.topics || 'the key concepts and skills in ' + v.subject} using a ${v.format || 'comprehensive outline'} format.${v.depth ? ' Depth level: ' + v.depth : ''}

Study Guide Content:

1. CORE CONCEPTS
   - Define key terminology with clear, memorable explanations
   - Explain fundamental principles and how they connect
   - Show relationships between concepts using diagrams or analogies

2. KEY THEORIES AND FRAMEWORKS
   - Main theories with their originators and core propositions
   - Critical evaluation of each theory — strengths and limitations
   - Real-world applications demonstrating each concept

3. PRACTICAL APPLICATIONS
   - Step-by-step problem-solving approaches with worked examples
   - Common scenarios and how to handle them correctly
   - Practice questions with detailed solutions and explanations

4. STUDY AIDS
   - Mnemonics and memory techniques for key terms
   - Visual diagrams, mind maps, or flowcharts
   - Key formulas, equations, or frameworks to memorize
   - Common mistakes to avoid on exams

5. REVIEW AND SELF-ASSESSMENT
   - Chapter summaries highlighting the 3 most important takeaways each
   - Review questions testing understanding — not just recall
   - Practice test with answer key and explanations

Constraints:
- Each concept must include a definition, example, and connection to the broader subject
- Avoid unnecessary details — focus on what is most testable or applicable
- Include memory aids for at least 5 key terms or concepts
- Provide practice questions at varying difficulty levels
- Tone: Clear, encouraging, and pedagogically effective. Write as if tutoring a student one-on-one.`;
            break;
          }
          case 'twitter-thread': {
            if (!v.topic) break;
            output = `You are a social media content strategist. Write an engaging Twitter/X thread about ${v.topic}.

Context: The thread targets an audience interested in ${v.topic}. The goal is to educate, engage, and drive discussion. The hook should stop the scroll and compel users to read all tweets.

Thread Structure:

1/${v.hook || `I've been thinking about ${v.topic} and here is what I learned`}

2/The most common misconception about ${v.topic}:
[State what most people get wrong]

3/[First key insight — include a specific data point, example, or framework]

4/[Second key insight — build on the first with a practical takeaway]

5/[Third insight — offer a counterintuitive perspective or pro tip]

6/[Real example, case study, or personal experience that illustrates the point]

7/[Actionable advice — something readers can apply immediately]

8/Summary: [Single sentence capturing the main takeaway]

${v.cta ? '\n' + v.cta : '\nWhat is your experience with this? Share your thoughts below 👇'}

Constraints:
- Each tweet must not exceed 280 characters — count carefully
- Open with a bold, curiosity-gap hook in tweet 1
- Number each tweet (1/8, 2/8, etc.) for clear progression
- Use line breaks within tweets for readability
- Limit relevant hashtags to 1-2 per tweet, 3 total across the thread
- End with a question or CTA to drive engagement
- Space tweets 2-3 minutes apart for maximum reach
- Tone: Conversational, insightful, and slightly provocative. Write with authority but approachability.`;
            break;
          }
          case 'linkedin-post': {
            if (!v.topic) break;
            output = `You are a LinkedIn content strategist and thought leader. Write a professional LinkedIn post about ${v.topic}.

Context: The post targets ${v.audience || 'LinkedIn professionals'} who are interested in ${v.topic}. The goal is to spark meaningful discussion and position the author as a credible voice in the space.

Personal Angle: ${v.angle || 'Share your personal experience, insight, or lesson learned'}

Post Structure:

HEADLINE: [First 1-3 lines that grab attention — make it bold, specific, and relatable]

[Open with a personal story, observation, or surprising fact relating to ${v.topic}]

[Share the key insight or lesson learned — be specific about what changed your thinking]

[Provide actionable advice or a framework readers can apply today]

Call to action: ${v.cta || 'Share your thoughts in the comments below — I would love to hear your perspective'}

[3-5 relevant hashtags]

Constraints:
- Write in first person for authenticity and connection
- Keep paragraphs short — maximum 3 sentences each
- Include line breaks between sections for mobile readability
- Lead with the most compelling idea — do not bury the lede
- Be specific — include numbers, timelines, or concrete examples
- Avoid corporate jargon and buzzwords — sound like a human, not a brand
- Tag 1-2 relevant people or companies if applicable
- Tone: Professional but conversational. Authoritative but approachable. Write to start a conversation, not make a speech.`;
            break;
          }
          default: {
            const parts = [];
            Object.entries(v).forEach(([key, val]) => {
              if (val && val.trim()) {
                const field = tpl.fields.find(f => f.key === key);
                parts.push(`${field?.label || key}: ${val}`);
              }
            });
            if (parts.length > 0) {
              output = `You are an expert in this domain.\n\nContext: The task involves ${parts[0].split(': ').slice(1).join(': ') || 'the specified topic'}.\n\nTask:\n${parts.map(p => p).join('\n')}\n\nConstraints:\n- Follow the specified format strictly\n- Provide specific, actionable output\n- Use a professional and clear tone throughout\n- Do not include unnecessary preamble or fluff`;
            }
            break;
          }
        }

        templateOutput.value = output || 'Fill in the fields above to generate a prompt...';
      }

      btnTemplateBack.addEventListener('click', () => { templateDetail.classList.add('hidden'); activeTemplate = null; });
      btnTemplateCopy.addEventListener('click', async () => {
        if (!templateOutput.value) return;
        try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText(templateOutput.value); } catch { templateOutput.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); }
        const orig = btnTemplateCopy.textContent;
        btnTemplateCopy.textContent = 'Copied!';
        setTimeout(() => { btnTemplateCopy.textContent = orig; }, 1500);
      });

      // ── Analyzer ──
      const analyzerInput = document.getElementById('analyzer-input');
      const btnAnalyze = document.getElementById('btn-analyze');
      const analyzerCharCount = document.getElementById('analyzer-char-count');
      const scoreValue = document.getElementById('score-value');
      const scoreLabel = document.getElementById('score-label');
      const scoreRingFill = document.getElementById('score-ring-fill');
      const scoreWords = document.getElementById('score-words');
      const criteriaList = document.getElementById('criteria-list');
      const suggestionsList = document.getElementById('suggestions-list');
      const analyzerImprovedCard = document.getElementById('analyzer-improved-card');
      const analyzerImproved = document.getElementById('analyzer-improved');
      const btnAnalyzerCopy = document.getElementById('btn-analyzer-copy');
      const btnAnalyzerUse = document.getElementById('btn-analyzer-use');

      analyzerInput.addEventListener('input', () => { analyzerCharCount.textContent = analyzerInput.value.length + ' characters'; });

      function getScoreColor(score) {
        if (score >= 80) return 'oklch(0.55 0.18 145)';
        if (score >= 60) return 'oklch(0.6 0.18 85)';
        if (score >= 40) return 'oklch(0.65 0.18 45)';
        return 'oklch(0.65 0.18 25)';
      }

      function getScoreCategory(score) {
        if (score >= 80) return 'Strong';
        if (score >= 60) return 'Good';
        if (score >= 40) return 'Fair';
        return 'Needs Work';
      }

      function renderAnalysis(result) {
        const circumference = 326.7;
        scoreRingFill.style.strokeDashoffset = circumference - (result.score / 100) * circumference;
        scoreRingFill.style.stroke = getScoreColor(result.score);
        scoreValue.textContent = result.score;
        scoreLabel.textContent = `${getScoreCategory(result.score)} - ${result.feedback}`;
        scoreWords.textContent = result.wordCount;

        criteriaList.innerHTML = result.criteria.map(c =>
          `<div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs py-1.5 border-b border-default last:border-0">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 min-w-0">
              <span class="${c.passed ? 'text-emerald-400' : 'text-tertiary'} font-mono w-4 shrink-0">${c.passed ? '\u2713' : '\u25CB'}</span>
              <span class="text-primary truncate">${c.label}</span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-secondary shrink-0 ml-2">${c.weight}%</span>
          </div>`
        ).join('');

        if (result.improvements.length > 0) {
          suggestionsList.innerHTML = `<p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-2">Add these missing elements to improve your prompt:</p>` +
            result.improvements.map(s => {
              const c = result.criteria.find(cr => cr.label === s);
              return `<div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs py-1.5 border-b border-default last:border-0">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">\u2192</span>
                <div class="min-w-0">
                  <span class="text-primary">${s}</span>
                  <p class="text-tertiary mt-0.5">${c ? c.description : ''}</p>
                </div>
              </div>`;
            }).join('');
        } else {
          suggestionsList.innerHTML = '<p class="text-xs text-emerald-400">All criteria met. Your prompt is well-structured.</p>';
        }

        if (result.score < 100) {
          analyzerImprovedCard.classList.remove('hidden');
          analyzerImproved.value = improvePrompt(analyzerInput.value, result);
        } else {
          analyzerImprovedCard.classList.add('hidden');
        }
      }

      function improvePrompt(original, result) {
        const imp = result.improvements;
        let improved = original;
        if (imp.includes('Role Assignment') && !imp.includes('Clear Objective')) improved = `You are an expert in this domain.\n\n${improved}`;
        if (imp.includes('Background Context')) improved = `Context: Provide relevant background information here.\n\n${improved}`;
        if (imp.includes('Constraints & Rules')) improved = `${improved}\n\nConstraints:\n- Follow the specified format strictly\n- Stay within the defined scope`;
        if (imp.includes('Output Format')) improved = `${improved}\n\nFormat your response as specified below.`;
        if (imp.includes('Tone & Style')) improved = `${improved}\n\nTone: Professional and clear.\nStyle: Direct and actionable.`;
        return improved;
      }

      btnAnalyze.addEventListener('click', () => { const text = analyzerInput.value.trim(); if (text) renderAnalysis(analyzePrompt(text)); });
      btnAnalyzerCopy.addEventListener('click', async () => {
        if (!analyzerImproved.value) return;
        try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText(analyzerImproved.value); } catch { analyzerImproved.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); }
        const orig = btnAnalyzerCopy.textContent;
        btnAnalyzerCopy.textContent = 'Copied!';
        setTimeout(() => { btnAnalyzerCopy.textContent = orig; }, 1500);
      });

      btnAnalyzerUse.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (!analyzerImproved.value) return;
        frameworkValues = {};
        selectedFramework = FRAMEWORKS.FREE;
        frameworkSelect.value = FRAMEWORKS.FREE;
        renderFields(FRAMEWORKS.FREE);
        const promptField = varFields.querySelector('[data-fkey="prompt"]');
        if (promptField) { promptField.value = analyzerImproved.value; frameworkValues.prompt = analyzerImproved.value; }
        compileGenerator();
        switchMethod('generator');
      });

      // ── Sanitizer ──
      const saniInput = document.getElementById('sani-input');
      const saniOutput = document.getElementById('sani-output');
      const saniBackticks = document.getElementById('sani-backticks');
      const saniFluff = document.getElementById('sani-fluff');
      const saniSpaces = document.getElementById('sani-spaces');
      const saniCopy = document.getElementById('sani-copy');
      const saniMarkdown = document.getElementById('sani-markdown');
      const saniQuotes = document.getElementById('sani-quotes');
      const saniUnicode = document.getElementById('sani-unicode');

      function applySanitizer(fn) { const input = saniInput.value; if (input) saniOutput.value = fn(input); }
      saniBackticks.addEventListener('click', () => applySanitizer(stripBackticks));
      saniFluff.addEventListener('click', () => applySanitizer(removeFluff));
      saniSpaces.addEventListener('click', () => applySanitizer(collapseSpaces));
      saniMarkdown.addEventListener('click', () => applySanitizer(stripMarkdown));
      saniQuotes.addEventListener('click', () => applySanitizer(fixSmartQuotes));
      saniUnicode.addEventListener('click', () => applySanitizer(stripUnicode));
      saniCopy.addEventListener('click', async () => {
        if (!saniOutput.value) return;
        try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText(saniOutput.value); } catch { saniOutput.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); }
        const orig = saniCopy.textContent;
        saniCopy.textContent = 'Copied!';
        setTimeout(() => { saniCopy.textContent = orig; }, 1500);
      });

      // ── State from URL ──
      const state = getStateFromURL();
      if (state && state.tool === 'generator' && state.framework) {
        if (Object.values(FRAMEWORKS).includes(state.framework)) {
          selectedFramework = state.framework;
          frameworkSelect.value = state.framework;
          frameworkValues = state.values || {};
          renderFields(selectedFramework);
        }
        switchMethod('generator');
      }

      // ── Keyboard shortcuts ──
      document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
        const tag = e.target.tagName;

        if ((e.ctrlKey || e.metaKey) && e.key === 'Enter') {
          if (!panels.generator.classList.contains('hidden') && tag === 'INPUT') {
            e.preventDefault(); compileGenerator(); return;
          }
          if (!panels.analyzer.classList.contains('hidden') && tag === 'TEXTAREA') {
            e.preventDefault(); btnAnalyze.click(); return;
          }
        }

        if ((e.ctrlKey || e.metaKey) && e.shiftKey && (e.key === 'C' || e.key === 'c')) {
          if (!panels.generator.classList.contains('hidden') && genOutput.value) { e.preventDefault(); btnGenCopy.click(); return; }
          if (!panels.templates.classList.contains('hidden') && templateOutput.value) { e.preventDefault(); btnTemplateCopy.click(); return; }
          if (!panels.analyzer.classList.contains('hidden') && analyzerImproved.value) { e.preventDefault(); btnAnalyzerCopy.click(); return; }
        }

        if (e.key === 'Escape') {
          if (!templateDetail.classList.contains('hidden')) { e.preventDefault(); btnTemplateBack.click(); return; }
        }

        if (!e.ctrlKey && !e.metaKey && tag !== 'INPUT' && tag !== 'TEXTAREA') {
          if (e.key === '1') { e.preventDefault(); switchMethod('generator'); }
          else if (e.key === '2') { e.preventDefault(); switchMethod('templates'); }
          else if (e.key === '3') { e.preventDefault(); switchMethod('analyzer'); }
        }
      });

      // ── Featured Prompts (top 6 on homepage) ──
      const featuredIds = ['code-reviewer','blog-writer','product-description','okr-planner','explainer','content-calendar','decision-maker','design-system-guide','resume-builder','productivity','sleep-hygiene'];
      const featured = featuredIds.map(id => PROMPTS.find(p => p.id === id)).filter(Boolean);
      const promptsSection = document.getElementById('prompts-section');

      function escHtml(s) {
        return s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;').replace(/"/g,'&quot;');
      }

      promptsSection.innerHTML = featured.map(p => {
        const escaped = escHtml(p.prompt);
        return `
        <div class="template-card prompt-card">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-primary">${escHtml(p.title)}</h4>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">${escHtml(p.desc)}</p>
          <pre class="prompt-preview hidden mt-2 p-2 rounded text-xs bg-surface leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap text-secondary border border-default overflow-x-auto">${escaped}</pre>
          <button class="btn-ghost mt-2 text-xs copy-prompt-btn" data-prompt="${escaped}">Copy Prompt</button>
        </div>`;
      }).join('');

      document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        const card = e.target.closest('.prompt-card');
        if (card && !e.target.closest('.copy-prompt-btn')) {
          const preview = card.querySelector('.prompt-preview');
          if (preview) preview.classList.toggle('hidden');
          return;
        }
        const copyBtn = e.target.closest('.copy-prompt-btn');
        if (copyBtn && copyBtn.dataset.prompt) {
          navigator.clipboard.writeText(copyBtn.dataset.prompt).catch(() => {});
          const orig = copyBtn.textContent;
          copyBtn.textContent = 'Copied!';
          setTimeout(() => { copyBtn.textContent = orig; }, 1200);
        }
      });
      renderCategories();
      renderTemplates();
      renderFields(selectedFramework);
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
